cs.IT, cs.OH, cs.NI, cs.PH, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the achievable rates and signal detection for optical wireless communication, which involves information transmission and processing. 
2. cs.OH (Other Computer Science) - The paper deals with a specific application of computer science, namely optical wireless communication, which may not fit into other sub-categories. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the practical receiver for optical wireless communication, which involves networking and communication technologies. 
4. cs.PH (Physics and Society) - The paper deals with the physical aspects of optical wireless communication, such as photon counting and photomultiplier tube amplification. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the performance evaluation of different signal detection methods, which may be relevant to multimedia applications.
